ir legacy reverberates throughout central Europe today. The book is an important study of the largest recorded episode of what we now call "ethnic cleansing," and it may also be the most significant untold story of the Second World War.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aForced migrationxHistoryx20th centuryxCzech Republic. 0aForced migrationzCzech RepublicxHistoryy20th century. 0aGermansxHistoryx20th centuryxCzech RepublicxSudetenland. 0aGermanszCzech RepubliczSudetenlandxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopulation transfersxGermansxHistoryx20th century. 0aPopulation transfersxGermansxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xForced repatriation. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018376440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183764423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300183764/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles